** About the Company **   
  
Davidson Technology are currently supporting a State Government Authority to
secure an experienced AO6 Application Support Analyst to provide operational
application support across all business applications and includes break fix,
project and development work.  
  
  
  
  
** About the Role **   
  
As the Application Support Analyst, you'll play a key role in ensuring the
smooth operation and optimisation of business applications by providing
responsive technical support, conducting routine system checks, and
undertaking administration and maintenance tasks. You will manage information
security requirements and collaborate with stakeholders to ensure the
alignment of application software enhancements with ITIL or software
development frameworks. With a proactive approach, you'll autonomously
coordinate operational project work packages, provide advanced application
advice and support services, and lead the development of application-specific
documentation and training materials. Additionally, you will liaise with
external vendors to resolve issues and contribute to the continuous
improvement of application products and services, whilst also managing
disaster recovery documentation and testing.  
  
  
  
  
** About You **   
  
To be successful you'll possesses a diverse skill set encompassing enterprise
and cloud application design, testing, implementation, and support, with
proficiency in SQL Server, Azure Applications, and Power Platform, and any
experience in Oracle is advantageous. You'll exhibit expertise in application
development platforms and frameworks such as .Net and Microsoft DevOps,
coupled with experience in leading application management functions including
change control, release management, continuous improvement, and project
management. Known for your ability to produce high-quality reports and
documentation, you'll excel in team environments, fostering effective working
relationships with internal and external stakeholders whilst maintaining a
steadfast commitment to business outcomes and customer-focused service
delivery in the ICT domain.  
  
  
  
  
** The Benefits **   
  
You will be offered a 5-year Fixed Term Contract with a salary of $110,217 -
$117,694 per annum plus Super.  
  
  
  
